President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the Commonwealth of Puerto Rico and ordered Federal assistance to aid in recovery efforts following a severe storm and flooding on September 13, 2020. The declaration makes Federal funding available to affected individuals in the Municipality of Arecibo. Assistance can include grants for temporary housing and home repairs, low-cost loans for uninsured property losses, and other programs to aid in recovery. Claude Hyacinthe has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for Federal recovery operations in the affected areas, and additional designations may be made in the future based on damage assessments. Residents and business owners who experienced losses can apply for assistance online or by phone. The toll-free telephone numbers will operate seven days a week from 7:00 a.m. to 9:00 p.m. local time. For further information, contact the FEMA News Desk.